comment_data.body: I am getting these regularly. I really don't see a specific pattern for when these errors occur, I am usually having an emulator open and IntelliJ running a debug session.
You can eliminate the error by disabling the embedded DevTools option in Settings/Preferences. It is the bottom one in the Experimental section.

@torlarse it looks like there may have been a problem with loading JxBrowser classes initially. Could you attach your logs so I can check if there were any error messages during class loading? If you go to Help > Show log in finder/explorer, there should be a file named `idea.log` or `idea`.
@helin24 Thanks, I sent a file link to the gmail-address in your Github profile :)

@torlarse thanks! I actually don't see any attempt to install JxBrowser in your logs. That would explain the problem, but I'll have to investigate why. Your project definitely has a pubspec.yaml file with a dependency on flutter, right?

My pubspec.yaml:

```
description: A new Flutter project.

version: 1.0.0+1

environment:
  sdk: ">=2.9.0 <3.0.0"

dependencies:
  flutter:
    sdk: flutter

  provider: ^4.0.0
  google_maps_flutter: ^1.0.3
  http: ^0.12.1
  json_serializable: ^3.5.1 
  location: ^3.2.4
  google_maps_webservice: ^0.0.19
  uuid: ^2.2.2

  cupertino_icons: ^1.0.0

dev_dependencies:

flutter:
```
